    "body": "Refactored the monolithic `jules_client.py` (919 lines) into a modular architecture following Single Responsibility Principle, with comprehensive test coverage and type hints throughout.\n\n## Structure\n\n- **`config.py`**: Centralized constants (API URLs, timeouts, state sets, default prompts)\n- **`data_classes/`**: Separated enums (`AutomationMode`, `SessionState`) and models (`Session`, `Activity`, `Plan`, `PullRequest`, `DedupResult`)\n- **`utils/`**: Extracted reusable functions (`prompt_fingerprint`, `check_for_duplicate`, `log_activity`)\n- **`sources/`**: `SourcesAPI` for repository operations\n- **`sessions/`**: `SessionsAPI` and `ActivitiesAPI` for session/activity management\n\n## Testing\n\n- **10 tests** covering config, data classes, utils, sources, and sessions\n- **pytest + pytest-cov** with coverage reporting\n- `requirements.txt` with core (`requests`) and dev dependencies\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nExisting code works unchanged:\n\n```python\nfrom jules import JulesClient\n\nclient = JulesClient()\nsession = client.create_session(...)  # Still works\n```\n\nNew modular access also available:\n\n```python\nclient = JulesClient()\nsource = client.sources.find_source_for_repo(\"owner\", \"repo\")\nsession = client.sessions.create_session_safe(...)\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n- `MODULAR_STRUCTURE.md`: Architecture overview, migration guide, examples\n- `tests/README.md`: Testing documentation\n- Type hints and docstrings throughout (PEP 8 compliant)",
